Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 325 degrees.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Cut chicken lengthwise into 1-inch strips. Place chicken on a #plate{}; coat with 1 TBSP tempura batter mix.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches the consistency of whole milk.

In a separate medium bowl, combine @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, remaining @tempura batter{82%g}, remaining Fry Seasoning, a pinch of salt, and pepper.

Working in batches, dip coated chicken into sour cream mixture until fully coated; shake off any excess liquid. Press each piece into tempura mixture until fully coated; shake off any excess mixture. Return fully coated chicken to plate.

Heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a #large heavy bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of tempura mixture sizzles when added to the pan, working in batches, add coated chicken in an even layer. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then reduce heat to medium and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.)

Transfer chicken to a #paper towel lined plate{}; season with salt.

> AIR FRYER ALTERNATIVE: Coat an #air fryer basket{} with cooking spray; arrange coated chicken side by side in basket. Coat tops of chicken with cooking spray. Air fry at 370 degrees for 8 minutes. Flip chicken and coat again with cooking spray; air fry until cooked through and crispy, 8 minutes more.

== Red Pepper Butter ==

While chicken cooks, place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{20-25%seconds}.

Stir @red pepper jam{1} into bowl with softened butter until smooth and thoroughly combined. Set aside until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you like your butter a bit more firm, place it in the fridge until ready to serve.

== Assembly ==

Spread out @Belgian waffles{4} in a single layer on a #baking sheet{}. Toast until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide waffles between #plates{}; spread each with as much red pepper butter as you like. Place chicken over top or on the side. Drizzle with as much @Mike's Hot Honey®{3/4%ounce} as you like and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.